<h2 id="comments">Comments</h2>

<div id="c1">
<p>Taking a top-down view of this issue sounds like an excellent idea. Generalization is a necessity in deciding what to eat.</p>

<p>According to <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0743266420/sr=8-1/qid=1154369227/ref=pd_bbs_1/002-8919127-9338409?ie=UTF8" rel="nofollow">Amazon&#8217;s review</a>, Willett stresses the following overarching advice:</p>

<ul>
<li>eat <a href="http://www.medical-library.net/sites/framer.html?/sites/carbohydrates_in_nutrition.html" rel="nofollow">complex carbohydrates</a> (though potatoes don&#8217;t count)</li>
<li>eat more vegetables</li>
<li>emphasize healthy fats (nuts/seeds/fish?)</li>
<li>eat small amounts of a tremendous variety of food</li>
<li>exercise</li>
</ul>

<p>That sounds like excellent starting advice.</p>

<p>Scott</p>

